==Dyirbal==
===Adjective===
'''gunga'''

# (''relevant to fruits or nuts that ripen in the sun'') [[ripe|Unripe]], green.
# (''used in cooking'') [[raw|Raw]], uncooked.
# (''relevant to humans and animals'') [[alive|Alive]].

'''Usage note:''' When translating Dyirbal into English, to use the term 'raw' is a [[rough]] [[translation]]; it may be better to say ''not yet ready for eating.'' So, if asking a Dyirbal speaker if something may be eaten ''gunga,'' you’ll be self-contradictive (like asking ''Can I eat this inedible thing?'').

===Antonyms===
*[[dungun]] (''ripe'')
*[[nyamu]] (''[[cooked]]'')
*[[buga]] (''[[dead]], [[rot|rotting]]'')

